      <title>Monotone Bounded Sequence Converges: Illustration</title>
   </titles>
   <body>
      <block>
         <block.body>
            <para>
               <para.body>If an increasing sequence <math>
                     <latex>(x_n)</latex>
                  </math> is bounded above, then <math>
                     <latex>(x_n)</latex>
                  </math> converges to a number in <math>
                     <latex>\RNr</latex>
                  </math>. Intuitively this is quite plausible as the graphic below shows.</para.body>
            </para>
            <media xmlns="Theorem" type="image" active="0" inline="0">
               <img xmlns="" src="ims/MonotoneBounded.png"/>
            </media>
            <para>
               <para.body>The sequence is increasing but gets squeezed below an upper bound. So it converges to the infimum of all upper bounds.</para.body>
            </para>
         </block.body>
      </block>
